{
  "stem": "11611.6",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Well, I talked to Heymann.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They made it really quite attractive.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The basic understanding was I'd function for about six months.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I would be responsible basically for setting the office up, hiring people, getting premises, and getting it started.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "No more than six months, on a contract basis, I would not be a regular employee of the Department of Justice.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I had cases involving the Department of Justice on the other side, tax cases.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We drafted a contract, which exempted those activities, so I could work for the Department of Justice and be suing it at the same time, and I did.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I was paid on an hourly basis at some midling-- I didn't give a damn what I was compensated at because my basic deal with the firm initially was whatever I got paid from the Department of Justice would be turned over to the firm and I would draw my normal partner's draw.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The contract provided that I'd be an ongoing partner of Arnold and Porter.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I wasn't going to quit Arnold and Porter because I knew they'd never take me back.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Anyhow, that's the way it worked.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "In fact, after awhile I spent so damn much time at the Office of Special Investigation that I revised my agreement with the firm against interest and treated it as basically a sabbatical, which cut my firm take down by half.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I thought I was cheating the firm.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I had a designated deputy [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] who was the heir apparent to begin with.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "After six months, he would take over and run the place and I hired some of the people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "He probably hired more.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we had a fairly good staff.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "First thing we lacked was a place to work.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
